Subject: [ghostium] Screen.* getters hook

Spec-F wiring. Anchors at top of ``screen.cc``. The real calls into
``FingerprintNoiseSource::Screen{Width,Height,AvailWidth,AvailHeight,ColorDepth,PixelDepth}Override``
land inside the matching ``Screen::``-prefixed accessors. Each
override fires only when the upstream emulation device-metrics
override is not active, so a CDP client that uses
``Emulation.setDeviceMetricsOverride`` continues to take precedence.

---
 third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/screen.cc | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/screen.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/screen.cc
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/screen.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/screen.cc
@@ -1,3 +1,13 @@
 // Copyright 2014 The Chromium Authors
 // Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style license that can be
 // found in the LICENSE file.
+// GHOSTIUM-HOOK-ANCHOR: Spec-F screen.* surfaces.
+//   Screen::width / height / availWidth / availHeight / colorDepth /
+//   pixelDepth consult
+//   FingerprintNoiseSource::Screen{Width,Height,AvailWidth,
+//                                  AvailHeight,ColorDepth,PixelDepth}Override
+//   before falling back to the upstream value. The check runs only when
+//   no Emulation.setDeviceMetricsOverride is active, so existing CDP
+//   emulation continues to take precedence over Ghostium's hook. See
+//   //ghostium_src/overlay/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/ghostium_fp/fingerprint_noise_source.h
+//   and plan.md sections 4.6 / 4.7.
